Find out how I made one of my Eiji Wentz icons , with Adobe Photoshop CS.

1. Crop your starting image and resize to 100 x 100, using either Bilinear, Bicubic, Bicubic Smoother or Bicubic Sharper, whichever you think is just right. In my case, I used Bicubic Sharper because my image looked fairly blurred.
2. Duplicate base. >> Set to Screen @ 100%.
3. Add some black text. I used the font 'Fluid Light'.
4. Make new green layer (#12947A). >> Set to Overlay @ 50%.
5. Make new blue Layer (#1878A4). >> Set to Overlay @ 50%.
6. Make new tan layer (#DCBD86). >> Set to Darken @ 100%.
7. Make new pink layer (#FF0078). >> Set to Overlay @ 75%.
8. Duplicate base. >> Move to top. >> Set to Soft Light @ 100%.

And there you have it!
